NSLOOKUP(1)                      User Commands                    NSLOOKUP(1)

NAME
       nslookup - query Internet name servers interactively

SYNOPSIS
       nslookup [-option] [name | -] [server]

DESCRIPTION
       Nslookup is a program to query Internet domain name servers.
       Nslookup has two modes: interactive and non-interactive.
       Interactive mode allows the user to query name servers for
       information about various hosts and domains or to print a list
       of hosts in a domain. Non-interactive mode is used to print
       just the name and requested information for a host or domain.

   NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
       Non-interactive mode is invoked when the name or Internet
       address of the host to be looked up is given as the first
       argument. The optional second argument specifies the host name
       or address of a name server.

   INTERACTIVE MODE
       Interactive mode is entered in the following cases:

       a) when no arguments are given (the default name server will
          be used)

       b) when the first argument is a hyphen (-) and the second
          argument is the host name or Internet address of a name
          server.

   INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
       host [server]
              Look up information for host using the current default
              server or using server, if specified.

       server domain
              Change the default server to domain; use the current
              default server to look up the address.

       lserver domain
              Change the default server to domain; use the initial
              server to look up the address.

       exit   Exits the program.

       set keyword[=value]
              This command is used to change state information that
              affects the lookups. Valid keywords are:

              all    Prints the current values of the frequently used
                     options to set. Information about the current
                     default server and host is also printed.

              class=value
                     Change the query class to one of:
                        IN   the Internet class
                        CH   the Chaos class
                        HS   the Hesiod class
                        ANY  wildcard

              [no]debug
                     Turn on or off the display of the full response
                     packets and any intermediate response packets
                     when searching.

              [no]d2
                     Turn debugging mode on or off. This prints
                     everything that debug prints plus the raw query
                     and reply packets.

              domain=name
                     Sets the search list to contain the single
                     domain name.

              [no]search
                     If the lookup request contains at least one
                     period but doesn't end with a trailing period,
                     append the domain names in the domain search
                     list to the request until an answer is received.

              port=value
                     Change the default TCP/UDP name server port to
                     value. The default value is 53.

              querytype=value / type=value
                     Change the type of the information query. The
                     default is A (IPv4 address). Possible values
                     include: A, AAAA, ANY, CNAME, HINFO, MX, NS,
                     PTR, SOA, SRV, TXT.

              [no]recurse
                     Tell the name server to query other servers if
                     it does not have the information.

              retry=number
                     Set the number of retries to number.

              timeout=number
                     Change the initial timeout interval for waiting
                     for a reply to number seconds.

              [no]vc
                     Use or do not use a virtual circuit (TCP) when
                     sending requests to the server.

              [no]fail
                     Try or do not try the next nameserver if a
                     nameserver responds with SERVFAIL.

OPTIONS
       Options can be given on the command line if they precede the
       host name (or hyphen):

       -type=TYPE / -query=TYPE / -querytype=TYPE
              Set the query type (A, AAAA, MX, NS, SOA, etc.).

       -class=CLASS
              Set the query class (default IN).

       -timeout=N
              Set the timeout in seconds.

       -retry=N
              Set the number of retries.

       -port=N
              Set the server port.

       -domain=NAME
              Set the search domain.

       -[no]debug
              Enable or disable debugging.

       -[no]d2
              Enable or disable exhaustive debugging.

       -[no]search
              Enable or disable use of the search list.

       -[no]recurse
              Enable or disable recursive queries.

       -[no]vc
              Enable or disable TCP for queries.

       -[no]fail
              Enable or disable trying next server on SERVFAIL.

EXAMPLES
       nslookup example.com
              Look up the A record for example.com.

       nslookup example.com 8.8.8.8
              Look up example.com using Google DNS server.

       nslookup -type=MX example.com
              Query MX records for example.com.

       nslookup -
              Enter interactive mode.

       nslookup
              Enter interactive mode with default server.

   INTERACTIVE SESSION EXAMPLE
              > set type=NS
              > example.com
              > server 8.8.8.8
              > example.com
              > set all
              > exit

SEE ALSO
       dig(1), host(1)

